article.headline: Cleveland State 84, John Carroll 65
article.story: CLEVELAND (AP) -- Joe Davis scored 17 points to lead four Cleveland State players in double figures as the Vikings rolled past cross-town Division III rival John Carroll 84-65 on Wednesday. Carlos English hit a 3-pointer with 14:57 left in the first half to give Cleveland State a 15-6 lead and the Blue Streaks couldn't catch up. A pair of free throws by Davis gave the Vikings (3-3) a 36-28 lead at the half. Cleveland State stretched the lead to 65-36 on another pair of Davis free throws with 11:08 left. Patrick Tatham added 11 points for Cleveland State while English and Raheem Moss finished with 10 apiece. Brandon Mimes led the Blue Streaks (1-2) with 10 points.
